<code class='bash'>
If I want to create an ann account in my Linux host, I run two commands:

sudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash ann
sudo passwd ann

After I have the ann account created, I can install heroku into the ann account:

ssh ann@localhost
cd ~
rm -rf heroku heroku-client.tgz heroku-client      heroku-linux-amd64.tar.gz
wget https://cli-assets.heroku.com/branches/stable/heroku-linux-amd64.tar.gz
tar zxf heroku-linux-amd64.tar.gz
echo 'export PATH=${HOME}/heroku/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc
bash
heroku auth:login
heroku status
</code>
